  <!-- ===== PAGE CONTENT (you can safely edit inside this block) ===== -->
  <main class="p-6 sm:p-10 lg:p-14">
    <!-- ===== START: Replace or add your page-specific content below ===== -->

    <div class="content-card mx-auto">
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-om-navy mb-4">Governance, Security, and Compliance</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-10 border-b pb-4">
            Robust governance and strong security are the cornerstones of this digital strategy, ensuring that initiatives are well-managed and risks are controlled. OMSB will institute multiple layers of oversight and align all activities with best practices and national regulations.
        </p>

        <!-- Digital Governance Structure -->
        <section class="bg-white shadow-xl rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-10 mb-10 card-hover transition duration-300">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold section-title text-om-teal mb-6">Digital Governance Structure</h2>
            <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700">
                OMSB will formalize a governance framework to oversee the digital transformation. This involves establishing dedicated bodies and clarifying roles to ensure clear strategic direction and accountability.
            </p>
            
            <div class="space-y-6">
                <!-- DTSC -->
                <div class="border-l-4 border-om-navy pl-4">
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl text-om-navy mb-1">Digital Transformation Steering Committee (DTSC)</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">
                        Chaired by a senior executive, this high-level committee provides **strategic direction**, prioritizes projects, approves key policies, and monitors progress/KPIs, reporting directly to the OMSB Board.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- IT Governance & Architecture Board -->
                <div class="border-l-4 border-om-navy pl-4">
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl text-om-navy mb-1">IT Governance & Architecture Board</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">
                        Focuses on **technical decisions**, including standards for systems, integration, architecture approvals, and managing exception requests.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <!-- Data Governance Committee -->
                <div class="border-l-4 border-om-navy pl-4">
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl text-om-navy mb-1">Data Governance Committee</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">
                        Responsible for **data standardization, data quality issues**, and ensuring data usage complies with privacy rules, with cross-department representation.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-6 text-sm italic text-gray-500">
                <span class="font-bold">Key Roles:</span> An Information Security Officer (or CISO) and a Chief Data Officer will be empowered to enforce policies. Clear **RACI matrices** will be defined for all major initiatives.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Policy Framework and Compliance -->
        <section class="bg-white shadow-xl rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-10 mb-10 card-hover transition duration-300">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold section-title text-om-teal mb-6">Policy Framework and Compliance</h2>
            <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700">
                OMSB will proactively update its internal policy framework to achieve **near 100% compliance** with the Government’s ICT controls by 2027 and align with international standards like ISO 27001.
            </p>

            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-3 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                <li><span class="font-semibold text-om-navy">Adoption of National Policies (By 2026):</span> Formal adoption of the **National Digital Accessibility Policy** and an **Internet Usage Policy** for employees.</li>
                <li><span class="font-semibold text-om-navy">Security Alignment:</span> Existing policies will be reviewed and strengthened in line with **ISO 27001** and Oman’s national cybersecurity framework.</li>
                <li><span class="font-semibold text-om-navy">Mandatory Documentation (By 2026):</span> Documenting an **Information Security Governance Framework** and an **ICT Business Continuity/Disaster Recovery Plan**.</li>
                <li><span class="font-semibold text-om-navy">Verification:</span> Conducting **annual IT audits** (internal or external) to verify compliance and identify gaps for remediation.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-6 text-sm italic text-gray-500">
                Achieving this level of policy alignment and proven compliance allocates a significant weight (40%) to institutional readiness under the Government Digital Transformation Excellence criteria.
            </p>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Cybersecurity Enhancements -->
        <section class="bg-white shadow-xl rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-10 mb-10 card-hover transition duration-300">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold section-title text-om-teal mb-6">Cybersecurity Enhancements</h2>
            <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700">
                Protecting the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of OMSB’s systems and data is paramount. The goal is to implement an **Information Security Management System (ISMS)** aligned with ISO/IEC 27001 standards by the late 2020s.
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <!-- Security Measures -->
                <div class="p-4 border border-gray-100 rounded-lg bg-blue-50/50">
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-om-navy mb-2">Technical Security Controls</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                        <li>**Access Controls:** Enforcing Role-Based Access (RBAC), Least Privilege principle, and **MFA** for administrators and sensitive system users.</li>
                        <li>**Encryption:** Encrypting data **at rest** (databases, storage) and **in transit** (using TLS for all web/app traffic).</li>
                        <li>**Testing:** Conducting **Vulnerability Assessments and Penetration Testing** on critical applications at least annually.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- Monitoring & Response -->
                <div class="p-4 border border-gray-100 rounded-lg bg-blue-50/50">
                    <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-om-navy mb-2">Incident Response & Monitoring</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 ml-4">
                        <li>**Incident Response:** Establishing a dedicated **Incident Response Team** and procedure, including periodic drills to test readiness.</li>
                        <li>**24/7 Monitoring:** Achieving a functional **Security Operations Center (SOC)** capability by 2028 (in-house or managed services).</li>
                        <li>**Target:** Achieving **ISO 27001 certification by 2028** as a strategic target.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-6 text-sm italic text-gray-500">
                Privacy protection is also key: new digital services will undergo **Privacy Impact Assessments (PIA)**, and ethical guidelines will accompany the introduction of emerging tech like **AI** to ensure fairness and auditability.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- Risk Management -->
        <section class="bg-white shadow-xl rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-10 mb-10 card-hover transition duration-300">
            <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold section-title text-om-teal mb-6">Risk Management</h2>
            <p class="mb-6 text-gray-700">
                Effective governance includes proactive risk management. OMSB will integrate digital transformation risks into its **Enterprise Risk Management (ERM) framework** to ensure the transformation stays on course.
            </p>

            <h3 class="font-semibold text-xl text-om-navy mb-3">Key Elements of Risk Management</h3>
            <div class="space-y-4">
                <div class="flex items-start">
                    <div class="text-om-gold mr-3 mt-1">&#9658;</div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">
                        **Risk Register:** A comprehensive risk register will be maintained, logging risks with their **likelihood and impact**, and assigning owners for mitigation. The DTSC will review this register in each meeting.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                    <div class="text-om-gold mr-3 mt-1">&#9658;</div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">
                        **Contingency Planning:** The governance bodies will execute contingency plans if any risk materializes (e.g., project delays), such as bringing in additional resources or adjusting timelines.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start">
                    <div class="text-om-gold mr-3 mt-1">&#9658;</div>
                    <p class="text-gray-700">
                        **Mitigation Examples:** For **change resistance**, heavy investment in communications and training; for **vendor risks**, clear SLAs, code escrow, and knowledge transfer clauses in contracts.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Summary -->
        <section class="bg-om-navy text-white rounded-xl p-8 shadow-xl">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">In Summary</h2>
            <p class="text-lg opacity-90">
                Strong governance, rigorous security, and strict compliance are **foundational** to OMSB’s digital strategy. By setting up the right committees and policies, OMSB creates an environment where digital initiatives can be executed in a controlled, transparent manner. These measures not only meet regulatory requirements but also instill a culture of **accountability and safety**, building confidence among stakeholders for sustainable digital transformation.
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>

